“No one is useless in this world who lightens the burden of it for anyone else.” 
#CharlesDickens On my bday this year I was able to do something I always wanted, to pay for a food truck to serve hot food in skid row through my favorite non-profit organization @wefeedthehungry which I’ve been a volunteer at for over a decade.  Trust they put all of your donations back into helping the skid row community so it can rise up. 🥰🥰🥰 This gentleman in the photo, I met in line in skid row where I volunteer Wednesday’s 12-2pm.  The first time was a few months back when he first arrived in The states with his family to have a better life. To make the story short, although he was skeptical and questioned our Dominican food that he devoured super fast, and a few weeks later, little did we know, he would have a job with #Latia  @karibbean_cuisine food truck.  What a lovely surprise!  I came to find out when I went to order food from #Latia and she said “oh I forgot to tell you, he works for me now.” He had mentioned he was a chef, I forgot to say that.  Hahaha 🤣🤣🤣 I love that fact that his happened and I would love to open up the doors for others through #Wefeedthehungry.  These are the kinds of stories I look on for Tv but rarely get any attention.  #goodnews so happy he has an income now to help his kids get going on the “American Dream.” As We all have to start some where. 🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽 thank you to @wefeedthehungry and to La Tia for making this happen @karibbean_cuisine You can see he is eating good too, con al Pansita 🤭 🙏🏽🙏🏽 #skidrow

“We live and we learn, if you choose to.” #morillism For all of those who have entered my life, those who have exited, or those who are still in it with me, I love you  and I’m beyond grateful for all our experiences, yes all. 🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽 More importantly I’m grateful for me today, for putting in the work the last 7 years to Heal myself.  To get rid of traumas, fears, misplaced understandings, anger, stereotypes, judgement, resentment, operating from the same victim mindset (which led to a depression), or plainly taking things personal. I have stayed consistent working on the beautiful person God created.  I mean, the amount of peace I feel today is unmatched to any other time of my life.  To be brutally transparent with you, I finally feel centered, grounded, and unstoppable.  In other words,  I have finally met who I really am, who I was created to be: A wonderful human to myself and to others with healthy boundaries.  I will entertain all of these new feelings because they are ones I want to keep holding on to.  Confidence, peace, fearlessness and the it list goes on.  I never understood when pastors meant when they said “renew your mind,” but today I sure do.  And more importantly I am proud of myself for not giving up, many times I could have, especially when I was faced with those impossible mountains(like witnessing my own child 🐶 being killed in front of my own eyes)  I had to climb, the last few years.  But I climbed with tears & bruises and kept going. I will continue climbing with a smile on my face, no matter how impossible the mountains looks in the present moment, I know I will finish as long as I continue to keep walking.  I no longer will be using my BRF, which I used to be known for.  I will get paid to show that face from now on🤭🤭🤭 I love you all and would like To say to myself, is a relief to finally meet me 🤣🙏🏽😍 lastly thank you for your patience for all of those who have stuck around. I know exactly how hard I made it for some of you, 🤷🏽‍♀️ I am grateful for you. And my inner work will never stop 🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽 Peace levels never stop. #headshots #theatrical
